039/**
040 * Defines constraint rules to be applied to an existing set of Metaschema
041 * module-based models.
042 */
043@SuppressWarnings({
044    "PMD.DataClass",
045    "PMD.FieldNamingConventions",
046    "PMD.ShortClassName"
047})
048@MetaschemaAssembly(
049    formalName = "External Module Constraints",
050    description = "Defines constraint rules to be applied to an existing set of Metaschema module-based models.",
051    name = "metaschema-module-constraints",
052    moduleClass = MetaschemaModelModule.class,
053    rootName = "METASCHEMA-CONSTRAINTS",
054    valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(lets = @Let(name = "deprecated-type-map",
055        target = "map { 'base64Binary':'base64','dateTime':'date-time','dateTime-with-timezone':'date-time-with-timezone','email':'email-address','nonNegativeInteger':'non-negative-integer','positiveInteger':'positive-integer' }"),
056        expect = @Expect(id = "metaschema-deprecated-types", formalName = "Avoid Deprecated Data Type Use",
057            description = "Ensure that the data type specified is not one of the legacy Metaschema data types which have been deprecated (i.e. base64Binary, dateTime, dateTime-with-timezone, email, nonNegativeInteger, positiveInteger).",
058            level = IConstraint.Level.WARNING, target = ".//matches/@datatype|.//(define-field|define-flag)/@as-type",
059            test = "not(.=('base64Binary','dateTime','dateTime-with-timezone','email','nonNegativeInteger','positiveInteger'))",
060            message = "Use of the type '{ . }' is deprecated. Use '{ $deprecated-type-map(.)}' instead.")))
061public class MetaschemaModuleConstraints implements IBoundObject {
062  private final IMetaschemaData __metaschemaData;
063
064  @BoundField(
065      description = "The name of this constraint set.",
066      useName = "name",
067      minOccurs = 1)
068  private String _name;
069
070  @BoundField(
071      description = "The version of this constraint set. A version string used to distinguish between multiple revisions of the same resource.",
072      useName = "version",
073      minOccurs = 1)
074  private String _version;
075
076  @BoundAssembly(
077      description = "Declares a set of Metaschema constraints from an out-of-line resource to import, supporting composition of constraint sets.",
078      useName = "import",
079      maxOccurs = -1,
080      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "imports", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
081  private List<Import> _imports;
082
083  @BoundAssembly(
084      formalName = "Metapath Namespace Declaration",
085      description = "Assigns a Metapath namespace to a prefix for use in a Metapath expression in a lexical qualified name.",
086      useName = "namespace-binding",
087      maxOccurs = -1,
088      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "namespace-bindings"))
089  private List<MetapathNamespace> _namespaceBindings;
090
091  @BoundAssembly(
092      useName = "scope",
093      minOccurs = 1,
094      maxOccurs = -1,
095      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "scopes", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
096  private List<Scope> _scopes;
097
098  public MetaschemaModuleConstraints() {
099    this(null);
100  }
101
102  public MetaschemaModuleConstraints(IMetaschemaData data) {
103    this.__metaschemaData = data;
104  }
105
106  @Override
107  public IMetaschemaData getMetaschemaData() {
108    return __metaschemaData;
109  }
110
111  public String getName() {
112    return _name;
113  }
114
115  public void setName(String value) {
116    _name = value;
117  }
118
119  public String getVersion() {
120    return _version;
121  }
122
123  public void setVersion(String value) {
124    _version = value;
125  }
126
127  public List<Import> getImports() {
128    return _imports;
129  }
130
131  public void setImports(List<Import> value) {
132    _imports = value;
133  }
134
135  /**
136   * Add a new {@link Import} item to the underlying collection.
137   *
138   * @param item
139   *          the item to add
140   * @return {@code true}
141   */
142  public boolean addImport(Import item) {
143    Import value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
144    if (_imports == null) {
145      _imports = new LinkedList<>();
146    }
147    return _imports.add(value);
148  }
149
150  /**
151   * Remove the first matching {@link Import} item from the underlying collection.
152   *
153   * @param item
154   *          the item to remove
155   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
156   */
157  public boolean removeImport(Import item) {
158    Import value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
159    return _imports != null && _imports.remove(value);
160  }
161
162  public List<MetapathNamespace> getNamespaceBindings() {
163    return _namespaceBindings;
164  }
165
166  public void setNamespaceBindings(List<MetapathNamespace> value) {
167    _namespaceBindings = value;
168  }
169
170  /**
171   * Add a new {@link MetapathNamespace} item to the underlying collection.
172   *
173   * @param item
174   *          the item to add
175   * @return {@code true}
176   */
177  public boolean addNamespaceBinding(MetapathNamespace item) {
178    MetapathNamespace value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
179    if (_namespaceBindings == null) {
180      _namespaceBindings = new LinkedList<>();
181    }
182    return _namespaceBindings.add(value);
183  }
184
185  /**
186   * Remove the first matching {@link MetapathNamespace} item from the underlying
187   * collection.
188   *
189   * @param item
190   *          the item to remove
191   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
192   */
193  public boolean removeNamespaceBinding(MetapathNamespace item) {
194    MetapathNamespace value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
195    return _namespaceBindings != null && _namespaceBindings.remove(value);
196  }
197
198  public List<Scope> getScopes() {
199    return _scopes;
200  }
201
202  public void setScopes(List<Scope> value) {
203    _scopes = value;
204  }
205
206  /**
207   * Add a new {@link Scope} item to the underlying collection.
208   *
209   * @param item
210   *          the item to add
211   * @return {@code true}
212   */
213  public boolean addScope(Scope item) {
214    Scope value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
215    if (_scopes == null) {
216      _scopes = new LinkedList<>();
217    }
218    return _scopes.add(value);
219  }
220
221  /**
222   * Remove the first matching {@link Scope} item from the underlying collection.
223   *
224   * @param item
225   *          the item to remove
226   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
227   */
228  public boolean removeScope(Scope item) {
229    Scope value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
230    return _scopes != null && _scopes.remove(value);
231  }
232
233  @Override
234  public String toString() {
235    return new ReflectionToStringBuilder(this, ToStringStyle.MULTI_LINE_STYLE).toString();
236  }

403                  binding = TargetedAllowedValuesConstraint.class),
404              @BoundGroupedAssembly(formalName = "Expect Condition Constraint", useName = "expect",
405                  binding = TargetedExpectConstraint.class),
